'''对流层顶'''是地球大气的[[对流层|对流层]]与[[平流层|平流层]]的分界面。

==定義==
[[Image:Earth_Atmosphere.svg|thumb]]
[[Image:Jetcrosssection.jpg|thumb]]
对流层顶是指气温不再随高度而变冷，而且几乎不含水蒸汽。[[世界气象组织|世界气象组织]]正式定义为:

{{Quotation|对流层与平流层的边界，[[气温垂直递减率|气温垂直递减率]]发生突然变化，其底界的气温垂直递减率小于等于2 °C/km，其上2km的平均气温垂直递减率不超过2 °C/km.<ref>{{cite book|title= International Meteorological Vocabulary|edition= 2nd|year= 1992|publisher= Secretariat of the World Meteorological Organization|location= [[Geneva|Geneva]]|isbn= 92-63-02182-1|page= 636}}</ref>}}

上述定义指出，大气垂直温度梯度的不连续性。<ref>{{cite book|last1= Panchev|first1= Stoǐcho|title= Dynamic meteorology|year= 1985|origyear= 1981|publisher= [[D._Reidel|D. Reidel Publishing Company]]|isbn= 90-277-1744-3|page= 129|chapter= Waves and instabilities in the atmosphere}}</ref>

==位置==
赤道的对流层平均高度17km，而极区的对流层平均高度9km。<ref>{{cite paper | last1 = Hoinka | first1 = K. P. | year = 1999 | title = Temperature, Humidity, and Wind at the Global Tropopause | journal = [[Monthly_Weather_Review|Monthly Weather Review]] | volume = 127 | pages = 2248{{spaced ndash}}2265 | publisher = [[American_Meteorological_Society|American Meteorological Society]]|bibcode = 1999MWRv..127.2248H |doi = 10.1175/1520-0493(1999)127<2248:THAWAT>2.0.CO;2 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title= Distribution and influence of convection in the tropical tropopause region|last1= Gettelman|first1= A.|last2= Salby|first2= M. L.|last3= Sassi|first3= F.|year= 2002|journal= [[Journal_of_Geophysical_Research|Journal of Geophysical Research]]|volume= 107|publisher= [[American_Geophysical_Union|American Geophysical Union]]|doi= 10.1029/2001JD001048|bibcode = 2002JGRD..107.4080G }}</ref>对流层的气温垂直递减率平均为6.5°C每千米。<ref name="Petty">{{cite book|last= Petty|first= Grant W.|title= A First Course in Atmospheric Thermodynamics|year= 2008|publisher= Sundog Publishing|location= [[Madison,_Wisconsin|Madison]], [[Wisconsin|WI]]|isbn= 978-0-9729033-2-5}}</ref>{{rp|112}} 在平流层，气温随高度增加而增加。   
 
民航班机一般飞行在平流层的底层，以避免云的影响。<ref name="Petty"/>{{rp|21}}

